        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 5:02PM EDT until July 24 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>SVRIWX

The National Weather Service in Northern Indiana has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Berrien County in southwestern Michigan...

* Until 530 PM EDT.

* At 501 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Lake Michigan
Beach, or near Benton Heights, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Benton Harbor, St. Joseph, Benton Heights, Watervliet, Coloma, Lake
Michigan Beach, Paw Paw Lake, Riverside, and Millburg.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 196 between mile markers 0 and 7.
Interstate 94 in Michigan between mile markers 33 and 42.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
